.TH "page_counter_memparse" 9 "page_counter_memparse" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
page_counter_memparse \- memparse() for page counter limits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" page_counter_memparse
.BI "(const char *buf "  ","
.BI "const char *max "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *nr_pages "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf" 12
string to parse
.IP "max" 12
string meaning maximum possible value
.IP "nr_pages" 12
returns the result in number of pages
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns -EINVAL, or 0 and \fInr_pages\fP on success.  \fInr_pages\fP will be
limited to PAGE_COUNTER_MAX.
